pass 2D pass 2NT pass 3D pass 3NT pass pass pass
[BCFlags "1f"]
[RotationNote "Board 2, chOption: E, chBasis: S, basisKind:Declarer, nOption:1, nBasis: 2, nRot: 3, useStandardVul: true"]
[VersionToken "a0522312d4d038e8c1444cba96cd416dee0b6dc19601b2a2c38832b02ff957bc"]
[Category "Bidding Conventions"]
[Difficulty "intermediate"]
[SkillPath "bidding_conventions/ogust"]
[Student "S"]
{You could just guess between pass, 3NT, or 5\D.

But you use Ogust instead. Partner responds 3\D.  

Partner's 3\D bid shows a minimum hand but a good suit, which should mean two of the top three honors. Your \DK tells you that partner has a 6-card \D  suit headed by the A Q. With three outside Aces you can count 9 tricks - you bid 3NT.}

[Event ""]
[Site ""]
[Date ""]
